The mnist-minimal data has just enough data to try out a simple convolutional network. However, as there are only 10 images, you will not get sensible results.

A very simple example configuration of a convolutional network for WEKA is given below. You will need to adjust the imagesLocation to give the path to the mnist-minimal folder on your system. The configuration can be pasted into WEKA's GUIs.

weka.classifiers.functions.Dl4jMlpClassifier -S 1 -iterator "weka.dl4j.iterators.ImageDataSetIterator -height 28 -imagesLocation wekaDeeplearning4j/data/mnist-minimal -numChannels 1 -bs 100 -width 28" -layers "weka.dl4j.layers.ConvolutionLayer -nFilters 5 -activation identity -adamMeanDecay 0.9 -adamVarDecay 0.999 -biasInit 1.0 -biasL1 0.0 -biasL2 0.0 -blr 0.01 -type VALID -cudnnAlgoMode PREFER_FASTEST -dist \"weka.dl4j.distribution.NormalDistribution -mean 0.001 -std 1.0\" -dropout 0.0 -epsilon 1.0E-6 -gradientNormalization None -gradNormThreshold 1.0 -kernelSizeX 5 -kernelSizeY 5 -L1 0.0 -L2 0.0 -name \"Convolution layer\" -lr 0.01 -momentum 0.9 -paddingX 0 -paddingY 0 -rho 0.0 -rmsDecay 0.95 -strideX 1 -strideY 1 -updater NESTEROVS -weightInit XAVIER" -layers "weka.dl4j.layers.DenseLayer -nOut 20 -activation relu -adamMeanDecay 0.9 -adamVarDecay 0.999 -biasInit 1.0 -biasL1 0.0 -biasL2 0.0 -blr 0.01 -dist \"weka.dl4j.distribution.NormalDistribution -mean 0.001 -std 1.0\" -dropout 0.0 -epsilon 1.0E-6 -gradientNormalization None -gradNormThreshold 1.0 -L1 0.0 -L2 0.0 -name \"Hidden layer\" -lr 0.01 -momentum 0.9 -rho 0.0 -rmsDecay 0.95 -updater NESTEROVS -weightInit XAVIER" -layers "weka.dl4j.layers.OutputLayer -activation softmax -adamMeanDecay 0.9 -adamVarDecay 0.999 -biasInit 1.0 -biasL1 0.0 -biasL2 0.0 -blr 0.01 -dist \"weka.dl4j.distribution.NormalDistribution -mean 0.001 -std 1.0\" -dropout 0.0 -epsilon 1.0E-6 -gradientNormalization None -gradNormThreshold 1.0 -L1 0.0 -L2 0.0 -name \"Output layer\" -lr 0.01 -lossFn LossMCXENT() -momentum 0.9 -rho 0.0 -rmsDecay 0.95 -updater NESTEROVS -weightInit XAVIER" -numEpochs 10 -algorithm STOCHASTIC_GRADIENT_DESCENT